This paper deals with the semantics of logic programs with abstract constraint atoms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and constraint programming. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses fixpoint-based and level mapping-based semantics, which are topics in logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of answer sets, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
